Metro AG (MEO) ,  Germany â€™s biggest
retailer, plans to combine its wholesale operations in  Pakistan 
with local competitor Makro-Habib Pakistan Ltd., the company
said today in an e-mailed statement.  Metro will hold a major part of the operational business
while Makro will have a majority in the real estate, according
to the statement. The deal is subject to regulatory approval,
Dusseldorf, Germany-based Metro said. The retailers have five
wholesale cash-and-carry stores each in the Asian country,
according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
